## Complete Command Sequence

For quick reference, here's the entire sequence:

```bash
# 1. Setup
mkdir -p ~/mcp-publisher-work
cd ~/mcp-publisher-work
git clone https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/registry.git
cd registry
go build -o ./bin/mcp-publisher ./cmd/publisher

# 2. Download files (manually or via curl)
# Place mcp_server_*.json files in ~/mcp-publisher-work/

# 3. Authenticate
./bin/mcp-publisher login github
# (Browser opens, approve GitHub authorization)

# 4. Validate
./bin/mcp-publisher validate ../mcp_server_cfo_agent.json
./bin/mcp-publisher validate ../mcp_server_trader_agent.json
./bin/mcp-publisher validate ../mcp_server_risk_agent.json

# 5. Publish
./bin/mcp-publisher publish ../mcp_server_cfo_agent.json
# (Domain verification prompt - follow instructions)
./bin/mcp-publisher publish ../mcp_server_trader_agent.json
./bin/mcp-publisher publish ../mcp_server_risk_agent.json

# 6. Verify
curl "https://registry.modelcontextprotocol.io/servers?search=aaos2"
```

